description:
Responsibilities:

              Report to CFO;
              Managing internal and external financial reporting requirements including consolidation, compliance and controlling activities;
              Managing parties including external auditors, tax authorities and internal business units;
              Leading cash and liquidity management and credit risk management;
              Leading forecasting and budgeting;
              Setting departmental KPIs for performance tracking;
              Coordinating company secretarial matters for the Group;
              Support various internal stakeholders in matters relating to internal controls, tax, and project implementations
              To perform additional duties and other ad hoc assignments as requested

Requirements:

              Degree holder in Accounting, Finance, Business Administration or related discipline, qualified accountant of HKICPA/ACCA
              At least 10-15 years in an all-rounded accounting function, experience with financial reporting and accounting with 5 years’ experience in managerial level
              Strong analytical ability and forecasting skills with strong attention to detail
              Knowledge in China accounting, laws and regulations
              Experience in Big4 or financial institutions is a plus
              Experience in medical related industry is a plus
              Proficient in both written and spoken English & Chinese
              Good time management skill and able to work under pressure
              Strong communication skills and connect proactively across various levels in the Business Units
              Proficient user in Excel
Interest parties please click "apply now" or please contact 3427 9018 for more information.

