Career Highlights: 

Monthly salary range from HK$20,000 (Officer) to HK$65,000 (Senior Manager), depend on Experience and Ability;
Senior Manager is require to manage a Team of Company Secretarial within the Company Secretarial Division;
Long terms career development in a Multinational Company;
5 days work with 20 days annual leave for the Senior Manager.

Key Responsibilities:    

Attending to ongoing compliance requirements for listed and non-listed, local and offshore companies;
Attending to ad hoc corporate transactions and providing relevant advice;
Keeping abreast of, monitoring, and analyzing developing trends and changes in regulatory compliance laws, rules and regulations, and advising clients of the operational impact and corporate governance matters. 

Key Requirements: 

Bachelor degree holder or above ;
Registered Student or Member of HKICS;
At least 8 years’ working experience in handling company secretarial matters of Hong Kong-listed companies, preferably with sizable professional firms or listed companies for the Senior Manager;
At least 3 years working experience in handling company secretarial matters for the Officer Grade;
Basic knowledge of Hong Kong listing rules and other relevant regulatory requirements for both listed and non-listed companies – essential;
Self-motivated, well-organized and detail-oriented;
Excellent command of spoken and written English with fluent spoken Mandarin;
Computer literate; experience with ViewPoint 7.4 preferred.
Candidates with Less Experience will be consider as Manager / Supervisor / Officer / Fresh Graduated Trainee position.



Attractive remuneration package commensurate with qualifications and experience will be offered to the right candidate. Interested parties please use the following "APPLY NOW" function to apply for the job. A full resume stating date of availability, current & expected salary are required.

Or email the Full Resume to dave @ talentcl.com

For any further inquiries about the job, please feel free to send message by WhatsApp at 9282 3326 (No telephone call will be answer).


All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.  Applicants not hearing from us within 3 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.

Responsibilities:

Oversee various accounting operations;
Manage Billing, Accounts Receivables, Accounts Payables, Cost Accounting, Inventory Accounting and Revenue Recognition;
Identify accounting and financial issues and suggest timely solutions;
Support month-end and year-end close process;
Manage quality control over financial transactions and reporting;
Manage the budgeting and forecasting;
Produce financial statements as requsted;
Coordinate the preparation of regulatory reporting;
Manage and comply with local, state, and federal government reporting requirements and tax filings;
Develop and adhere to policies and procedures.
Requirements:

Degree holder in Finance or Accounting, qualified CPA and associate member of HKICS / ICSA;
IPO / listed company experience is a must;
Strong analytical mind, good communication skill and business sense
Strong Microsoft Office application and Chinese word processing;
Good command of both written and spoken in English and Chinese, fluency in Putonghua is highly preferred.
We offer an attractive remuneration package to the right candidates. Interested parties please apply in full resume including current salary, expected salary and earliest availability by clicking APPLY NOW. 

Applications without expected salary will not be considered.
Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Full responsible to manage accounting team in Hong Kong, China and Overseas Group Companies (including but not limited to Singapore, European Countries) by streaming and enhancing the operational effectiveness and efficiency;
Be responsible for financial planning, tax planning, cost accounting, budgeting and forecasting, cash flow management, statutory & financial management report and internal control for the company;
Review, formulate and implement the internal control procedures and policies of the company operations;
Liaise with external auditors, legal and tax advisers;
Negotiate with banker for bank facilities;.
Manage Trade Mark Registration;
Make the recommendations on risk management and corporate governance issues to top management.

REQUIREMENTS

Degree holder in Accounting or related discipline;
Over 10 years financial exposure with more than 3 years working experience in in retail industry;
Well acquired with Hong Kong and PRC accounting and tax systems;
Pleasant personality, problem solving skills, good interpersonal skills, well-organized with high commitment, proactive, strategic thinking and analytical mind.
Flexible in working hours and ability to work under pressure in a demanding and fast pace environment;
Proficient in computer applications.
Proficient in English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua.
Immediate availability is preferred.

We offer 5-day work week and attractive remuneration package with birthday leave,  medical medical insurance, and discretionary bonus to the right candidate.

Interested parties please send your full resume with the date of availability and expected salary by email via clicking "Apply Now". Only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.
